{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-isic-1430"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Community Knitwear Manufacturing"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "1430"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :knitwear/manufacturing
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:fair-labor :local-industry :supply-chain-transparency]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :knitwear-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :cae]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies []
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "KnitwearAdvisor ⊣ KnitwearGovernor, langgraph-clj StateGraph
 (langgraph.graph, knitwear.operation/build), append-only audit ledger
 (knitwear.store/ledger + append-ledger!, MemStore). Fixes a prior gap:
 this blueprint claimed :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented, but
 there was no `operation.cljc` and no `langgraph.graph` usage anywhere
 in `src/` -- `knitwear.sim` hand-chained
 `advisor/*-proposal -> governor/evaluate` directly with plain function
 calls, a fake StateGraph worse than the usual deferred-stub pattern
 since no StateGraph was even attempted (zero `require` of
 `langgraph.graph`, zero use of `state-graph`/`add-node`/
 `compile-graph`), despite the real `io.github.com-junkawasaki/langgraph-clj`
 dependency already sitting correctly in `deps.edn`'s main `:deps` map.
 No audit-ledger append function existed anywhere in the codebase either
 -- only prose comments in other namespaces mentioned an audit ledger,
 aspirational, not real. Now: a genuinely compiled StateGraph
 (`:intake -> :advise -> :govern -> :decide -+-> :commit /
 :request-approval -> :commit / :hold`) with
 `interrupt-before #{:request-approval}` + in-memory checkpointer for
 real human-in-the-loop resume, and a real `knitwear.store/ledger` +
 `append-ledger!` genuinely wired into the `:commit`/`:hold` graph
 nodes. `knitwear.advisor`'s four proposal builders and
 `knitwear.governor`'s hard/soft checks (closed op-allowlist,
 effect-must-be-:propose, plant/batch verification chain,
 process-control-forbidden keyword block, safety-concern-always-
 escalates, confidence floor / high-stakes-actuation escalation) are
 reused UNCHANGED -- this fix only wires the existing knitwear domain
 policy into a real compiled graph and a real ledger, it does not
 redesign it. `knitwear.phase` (formerly a fake graph-topology-as-EDN
 stand-in, `ADVISOR-NODE`/`GOVERNOR-NODE`/`HOLD-NODE`/`COMPLETE-NODE`,
 that no graph ever consumed) is now a real 0->3 rollout auto-commit
 gate: phase 1 auto-commits maintenance scheduling only, phase 2 adds
 verified production-batch logging, phase 3 has the same auto-commit
 set because safety-concern flagging and shipment coordination NEVER
 auto-commit at any phase (two independent layers -- the Governor's own
 soft-violation gates AND `phase/never-auto-commit`). Proven end-to-end
 by `test/knitwear/operation_test.clj` (ledger stays empty until a real
 commit, hold-until-approved for both safety-concern and high-stakes
 shipment coordination, governor rejection blocks commit, phase-hold for
 clean-but-not-yet-eligible proposals) through the REAL compiled graph,
 plus a `clojure -M:dev-local:run` demo runner producing real ledger
 entries for every scenario. 54 tests / 194 assertions green
 (`clojure -M:dev-local:test`), clj-kondo 0 errors. CI
 (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`, sibling-checkout pattern for
 `:local/root` deps) was missing and is added in this fix."}
